  "identifier": "HB 631",
  "title": "AN ACT relating to school district calendars and declaring an emergency.",
  "abstract": "Provide 10 additional disaster relief student attendance days to provide instruction using alternate settings; allow local school districts to make up days missed by adding instructional time to student attendance days; require local boards of education seeking to revise its calendar to submit a plan for approval to the Department of Education; allow instructional time made up to count as employee contracted days; EMERGENCY.",
